    "body": "This definitely seems broken.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to restart after 40h/380 epochs of non-finality.  I've set heap size to 5GB (`-Xmx5g`): at 4GB the restart was spending most of the time in GC; at 5GB GC is very low.\r\n\r\nFrom the logs:\r\n```\r\n2020-06-22 09:22:06.442+00:00 | main | INFO  | teku-status-log | Initializing storage\r\n2020-06-22 09:23:23.032+00:00 | StorageUpdateChannel-0 | INFO  | Store | Process 6717 block(s) to regenerate state\r\n2020-06-22 09:23:27.574+00:00 | StorageUpdateChannel-0 | INFO  | Store | Processed 100 blocks\r\n2020-06-22 09:23:31.353+00:00 | StorageUpdateChannel-0 | INFO  | Store | Processed 200 blocks\r\n...\r\n2020-06-22 09:27:12.188+00:00 | StorageUpdateChannel-0 | INFO  | Store | Processed 6300 blocks\r\n2020-06-22 09:27:15.609+00:00 | StorageUpdateChannel-0 | INFO  | Store | Processed 6400 blocks\r\n2020-06-22 09:27:18.972+00:00 | StorageUpdateChannel-0 | INFO  | Store | Processed 6500 blocks\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt has now been stuck here for 40 minutes, at 80% CPU on 6 cores, and seems to be making no further progress.",
